  "sw_detailed": {
    "module_name": "EGTM_ATOM_3_Phase_Inverter_PWM",
    "public_functions": [
      {
        "signature": "void initEgtmAtom3phInv(void)",
        "behavior_description": "Initialize a unified EGTM PWM configuration for a 3‑phase complementary inverter and a separate single‑channel PWM used as ADC trigger. Steps: (1) Declare all configuration structures locally: the main IfxEgtm_Pwm_Config plus arrays for three logical inverter channels (IfxEgtm_Pwm_ChannelConfig[3]), their complementary output configuration (IfxEgtm_Pwm_OutputConfig[3]), and dead‑time configuration (IfxEgtm_Pwm_DeadTime or DTM config per channel). Also declare an InterruptConfig for the PWM base channel. In addition, declare a second minimal IfxEgtm_Pwm_Config with a single channel (ChannelConfig[1], OutputConfig[1]) dedicated to the ADC trigger output. (2) Initialize both config structs with defaults via the initConfig API. (3) For the 3‑phase inverter handle: set cluster to the specified EGTM cluster, select the ATOM submodule, configure center‑aligned operation, enable synchronous update, set the requested PWM frequency, and select the requested ATOM clock source and DTM clock source. Populate three logical channels with contiguous logical indices 0..2, each with complementary outputs, active‑high/low polarities as required, and assign dead‑time values matching the required 1 µs on both edges. Do not assign phase shift (center‑aligned). (4) Prepare InterruptConfig: set mode to pulse‑notification, isrProvider to CPU0, priority to the configured value, vmId to the configured value, and assign the periodEvent callback pointer to IfxEgtm_periodEventFunction; assign this InterruptConfig pointer only to the first (base) logical channel; set interrupt pointers for the remaining channels to NULL. (5) For the ADC trigger handle: configure a single logical channel set to edge‑aligned mode with 50% duty, non‑complementary output. Keep its frequency coherent with the inverter handle to maintain consistent timing. (6) Before touching hardware registers, check if the EGTM module is enabled; if not enabled, enable it and then enable the necessary EGTM clocks for the selected clock domain(s) using the CMU clock‑enable API. (7) Call the unified PWM init API for the 3‑phase inverter handle first, then for the single‑channel ADC‑trigger handle. The init applies pin routing from the configured output maps and applies the initial duties and dead‑time. (8) Route the trigger generated by the dedicated ADC trigger channel to the ADC trigger fabric using the EGTM Trigger API, selecting the specified trigger signal and channel. (9) Store persistent module state (driver handle, a persistent channels array, and current dutyCycles/deadTimes arrays) so that runtime updates can be applied later referencing that state. (10) Configure the debug I/O pin used by the ISR as a push‑pull output using the Port driver after PWM init has completed.",
        "driver_calls": [
          "IfxEgtm_Pwm_initConfig",
          "IfxEgtm_isEnabled",
          "IfxEgtm_enable",
          "IfxEgtm_Cmu_enableClocks",
          "IfxEgtm_Pwm_init",
          "IfxEgtm_Trigger_trigToAdc",
          "IfxPort_setPinModeOutput"
        ],
        "from_reference": true,
        "call_context": "init"
      },
      {
        "signature": "void updateEgtmAtom3phInvDuty(float32 *requestDuty)",
        "behavior_description": "Update the three inverter phase duties immediately and synchronously. Read three duty values from requestDuty[0..2] in percent, clamp each to [0, 100], and copy them into the module's persistent dutyCycles[3] state. Call the unified EGTM PWM immediate multi‑channel duty update API once, passing the dutyCycles array directly (percent values, no scaling). Do not perform any timing or scheduling within this function; it purely updates duty values and applies them immediately.",
        "driver_calls": [
          "IfxEgtm_Pwm_updateChannelsDutyImmediate"
        ],
        "from_reference": true,
        "call_context": "loop"
      },
      {
        "signature": "void interruptEgtmAtom(void)",
        "behavior_description": "ISR for the EGTM PWM period event routed internally by the unified driver. Keep the body minimal: toggle the configured debug output pin to allow runtime observation of PWM period interrupts. Do not call any driver interrupt handler from here; the unified driver routes interrupts via its internal mechanism.",
        "driver_calls": [
          "IfxPort_togglePin"
        ],
        "from_reference": false,
        "call_context": "none"
      },
      {
        "signature": "void IfxEgtm_periodEventFunction(void *data)",
        "behavior_description": "Unified EGTM PWM driver period event callback. This function must match the expected void*(data) signature. It performs no work; simply cast data to void to suppress unused warnings. The ISR handles any observable actions like pin toggling.",
        "driver_calls": [],
